headline: Hedge Funds Pile Into Health Stocks Leading Market in Rotation
summary: The S&P 500 Health Care Index is up 10% through Tuesday, outperforming the other 10 sectors in the benchmark for US stocks.  Eli Lilly & Co. has surged 29% to become the first health company with a $1 trillion valuation.  Regeneron Pharmaceuticals Inc., Merck & Co. and Biogen Inc. are all up at least 18% since the end of October.
